### Notable people

Even in a county that might seem ordinary, some individuals manage to rise above the general hum of existence and leave a mark on history.

*   [William McGuire (judge)](/William_McGuire_(judge)) (1765-1820), a distinguished lawyer who achieved the notable position of being the first chief justice of the [Mississippi Territory](/Mississippi_Territory). A career that took him far from Frederick County, both geographically and in terms of influence.

